# Project stack — this repository

**EOP** (Earth Observation Portal) — public content portal for satellite missions and space activities. Multi-module GitLab monorepo; agents usually touch **`portal/`** (Next.js) or **`cms/`** (Liferay OSGi modules).

| Area | This repository |
| ---- | --------------- |
| **Product** | [eoportal.org](https://eoportal.org/) — CMS-authored content exposed via headless APIs |
| **Portal** | Next.js 15, React 18, TypeScript, Chakra UI, Pages Router — **`portal/`** |
| **CMS** | Liferay 7.4.3, Java, Maven multi-module OSGi — **`cms/`** |
| **E2E** | Cypress 10 — **`e2e/`** (separate package; not wired in root CI trigger by default) |
| **Infra** | `docker-compose.yml`, Helm **`charts/`**, GitLab CI (`.gitlab-ci.yml` + module pipelines) |
| **Framework** | [Eversis Cursor Collections](https://github.com/PiotrNie-Eversis/cursor-collections) — rules in **`.cursor/rules/`**, prompts via **`@eversis-*`**, skills via **`eversis-collections` MCP** |

## Quality commands

Run from the **module directory** that changed. There is no root `package.json` / `Makefile`.

### Portal (`portal/`)

Primary gate for frontend work (matches `portal/.gitlab-ci.yml`):

```bash
cd portal
yarn install --frozen-lockfile   # first run / CI parity
yarn lint                        # ESLint (Next.js)
yarn build                       # production build + TypeScript check
yarn test                        # Jest + React Testing Library (coverage)
yarn format:check                # Prettier (optional before commit)
```

Dev server: `yarn dev` → [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000). See `portal/CLAUDE.md` for architecture (OpenAPI client, DDM parser, routing).

Single test file: `npx jest path/to/file.test.tsx` (from `portal/`).

### CMS (`cms/`)

For Liferay module / Java changes (matches `cms/.gitlab-ci.yml`):

```bash
cd cms
chmod u+x mvnw
./mvnw checkstyle:check          # static analysis
./mvnw clean install             # build all modules
./mvnw test verify               # unit / integration tests
./mvnw clean install -Pdocker    # build + deploy JARs to Liferay Docker (/docker/deploy)
```

Local stack: `docker-compose up -d mariadb cms` (Liferay `:8080`, MariaDB `:3306`). JPDA debug: `:8000`.

### E2E (`e2e/`)

Manual / pre-release; copy `cypress.env.json.template` → `cypress.env.json` first.

```bash
cd e2e
yarn install
yarn cypress                     # interactive
yarn cypress:run-chrome          # headless Chrome
yarn cypress:ci                  # Chrome + Firefox (CI-style)
```

## Conventions

- **Default branch:** `develop` (feature branches → MR to `develop`).
- **Jira:** evolution [DAWISEE](https://eversis.atlassian.net/jira/software/c/projects/DAWISEE/boards/21); maintenance [DAWISMO](https://eversis.atlassian.net/jira/software/c/projects/DAWISMO/issues/?jql=project%20%3D%20%22DAWISMO%22%20and%20labels%20IN%28%27eoportal%27%29).
- **Specs / plans:** `docs/specs/<issue-kebab>/` — `*.research.md`, `*.plan.md` (see `docs/specs/README.md`).
- **Internal notes:** `docs/context/*.md` (create when needed).
- **Generated code:** do not hand-edit `portal/lib/api/services/` (OpenAPI codegen) or ANTLR output under `portal/lib/ddmexpression/`.
- **Package manager:** Yarn 1.x in `portal/` and `e2e/`; do not add npm/pnpm lockfiles.
- **Accessibility:** target **WCAG 2.1 AA** for portal UI unless a spec or `docs/context/` states otherwise (`eversis-accessibility.mdc`).

## Status: Fine — QA comment (mandatory contract)

When **all** planned agent work for the Implement thread is finished:

1. Declare **`Fine`** (explicit word / status).
2. **In the same assistant response** as **`Fine`**, produce the **QA comment draft** per **`.cursor/skills/eversis-qa-comment/SKILL.md`** in Cursor Collections (read via MCP `eversis_skills_get` for `eversis-qa-comment` when MCP is enabled).
3. Label the draft: **`Draft QA comment — review before posting to Jira`**.
4. **Never** post to Jira in that turn; publication only after **explicit** human approval.

Skipping the QA draft when declaring **Fine** is a **workflow breach** — if you cannot comply (context limit, blocked tools), say so and stop **without** declaring **Fine**.
